name: Franklin ClearBridge Sustainable Global Infrastructure Income Fund
longDescription: In pursuing its investment objective, the underlying fund will generally invest at least 80 percent of its assets in equity securities of issuers engaged in the infrastructure business the funds sub-advisor generally considers an issuer to be engaged in the infrastructure business if at least 50 percent or more of its assets, income, sales or profits are committed to, derived from or related to the construction, renovation, ownership, development, financing, management or operation of infrastructure assets or the provision of raw materials necessary for the construction and maintenance of infrastructure assets; will invest primarily in income-paying securities. Franklin ClearBridge Sustainable Global Infrastructure Income Active ETF seeks to provide income and capital appreciation through exposure to global equity securities.
